content.text: 2GB mem in 112
Max_workers set to auto in app settings
running 4 scans in same time with 10m as biggest.

10m and 160k starts in the same time. 10m gets all resources and 160k stuck. 10m error due to memory leak and exit. 2m and 20k did not start and did not finished. 160k stays stuck and wont start/finish or exit. stopping the service will leave 2 process up.
10m and 160k still counting time in API call.
Service is down in the end of the test?
test2: 20-4 2pm, 01:00h (after restart)
10m and 160k starts in the same time. 10m got error after 9m and 160k after 2m. both exit normally. 20k finished and exit ok after 12m. 2m finish after 1h and exit all is fine.
test3: 20-4 3:50pm, 05:30h (after restart the service)
160k after 15s error and exit ok. 2m, 1h error exit ok. 20k, 1m finish ok. 10m error after 5h and exit ok,
test4: 20-4 23:40. 04:00h, (after restart the service)
10m got error and exit ok. 2m and 20k finished ok. 160k got error and did not finish, got stuck.
test5: 21-4 10:25 01:00h (after restart the service)
160k and 2m and 20k finished ok. 10m started and immediately stuck and did not exit ok. Killed the process after 8h. Stopping the service did not kill the 3 processes.
test6: 21-4 19:00 11:00h (after restart the service, Try with no auto for max workers)
10m, 160k, 2m all finished ok. 2m had error and exit.
Not
restart the service, no auto for max workers)
160k, 20k, 2m all finished fine. 10m got an error after 1h and exit fine.
test8: 22-4 13:15 10:00h (Restart the service, no auto for max workers)
Restarting the service created new process. Now there is 3!! Stopping the service leaves one service up - It is the fastAPI.
160k, 2m, 20k, 10m all finished ok. API fine.
test9: 23-4 10:00 01:12(Did NOT Restart the service, no auto for max workers)
160k, 2m, 20k, all finished ok. API fine. 10M got error and exit ok.
test10: 23-4 11:39 12:00h (Did NOT Restart the service, no auto for max workers)
All was fine.
test11: 24-4 12:15 01:00h (Did NOT Restart the service, no auto for max workers)
All done ok, 10m got erro and exit ok.
test12: 24-4 15:00 00:48h (Restart the service, no auto for max workers, 4 workers max)
2m and 10m got error and exit fine. rest done fine.
test13: 24-4 16:10 01:00h(Did NOT Restart the service, no auto for max workers, 4 workers max)
160k and 20k are fine. 2m with error exit ok. 10m stuck. In task manager we see 3 processes. In get API for 10m we get 0 in
"total_current_scanned_files": 0.
test14: 24-4 19:00 01:00h(Restart the service, no auto for max workers, 4 workers max)
All but 10m are fine. 10m stuck again. 3 process are up.
test15: 24-4 22:00 01:00h(Restart the service, no auto for max workers, 4 workers max)
All but 10m are fine. 10m stuck again. 3 process are up.
test16: 25-4 08:30 11:00h(Restart the service, no auto for max workers, 2 workers max)
All finished fine
